## 3. The File System Module (fs)

```js
const fs = require('fs')

// Create/write a file
fs.writeFileSync('hello.txt', 'Hello from Node.js!')

// Read a file
const data = fs.readFileSync('hello.txt', 'utf8')
console.log(data)
```

Your JavaScript can now **create real files on your computer** — not possible in the browser.

