## 4. Raw HTTP Server (Node without Express)

```js
const http = require('http')

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  if (req.url === '/') {
    res.write("Welcome home!")
  } else if (req.url === '/about') {
    res.write("This is the about page")
  } else {
    res.write("Page not found")
  }
  res.end()
})

server.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log("Server running on port 3000")
})
```

Key concepts:
- `req.url` — which path the user visited (`/`, `/about` etc.)
- `req.method` — what type of request (GET, POST etc.)
- `res.write()` — write a response
- `res.end()` — finish the response
- `server.listen(3000)` — start the server on port 3000

**localhost** = this machine itself (not the internet)
**Port 3000** = like a flat number in an apartment building — multiple servers on same machine use different ports

