## 6. Express Basics

### Setup
```bash
npm init -y
npm install express
```

### Basic server
```js
const express = require('express')
const app = express()

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send("Hello from Express!")
})

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log("Express server running on port 3000")
})
```

### res.send() vs res.json()
```js
res.send("Hello")           // plain text
res.json({ name: "Rahul" }) // JSON — used for APIs
```

### HTTP Methods
```
GET    → fetch/read data    → app.get()
POST   → send/submit data   → app.post()
PUT    → update data        → app.put()
DELETE → delete data        → app.delete()
```

