## 7. HTTP Status Codes

Always send the correct status code with your response:

```js
res.status(400).json({ error: "Bad request" })   // user sent wrong data
res.status(201).json({ message: "Created!" })     // something was saved
res.status(404).json({ error: "Not found" })      // route doesn't exist
res.status(500).json({ error: "Server error" })   // something broke
```

```
200 → OK (success)
201 → Created (something was saved)
400 → Bad request (user sent wrong data)
404 → Not found
500 → Server error
```

