## 11. Express Router (Organized Routes)

Split routes into separate files instead of putting everything in `server.js`.

**Folder structure:**
```
backend/
  server.js
  routes/
    users.js
    products.js
  models/
    User.js
  .env
  .gitignore
```

**routes/users.js:**
```js
const express = require('express')
const router = express.Router()

router.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.json([
    { id: 1, name: "ab" },
    { id: 2, name: "cd" }
  ])
})

router.get('/:id', (req, res) => {
  res.json({ userId: req.params.id })
})

module.exports = router   // export (like export default in React)
```

**server.js:**
```js
const usersRouter = require('./routes/users')  // import
app.use('/users', usersRouter)
// Now every route in users.js automatically starts with /users
```

