## 14. Route Parameters & Query Strings

### Route Parameters — for fetching a specific item
```js
router.get('/:id', (req, res) => {
  const id = req.params.id
  res.json({ userId: id })
})
```
Visit `/users/123` → `req.params.id` = `"123"`

### Query Strings — for filtering/searching
```js
router.get('/search', (req, res) => {
  console.log(req.query)
  res.json(req.query)
})
```
Visit `/users/search?city=jaipur&age=20` → `req.query` = `{ city: "jaipur", age: "20" }`

### Route Order Matters ⚠️
```js
// ✅ CORRECT — specific routes above dynamic ones
router.get('/search', ...)
router.get('/:id', ...)

// ❌ WRONG — /:id catches /search too!
router.get('/:id', ...)
router.get('/search', ...)  // never reached
```

