## 20. JS Concepts Revised

### Async/Await & Event Loop
```js
async function getUser() {
  console.log("A")
  const data = await fetch("https://api.example.com/user")
  console.log("B")
}

getUser()
console.log("C")

// Output: A → C → B
// await pauses that function but doesn't block everything else
```

### Higher Order Functions
A function that takes another function as an argument.
```js
[1,2,3].map(num => num * 2)         // map is a HOF
setTimeout(() => {}, 1000)          // setTimeout is a HOF
app.use((req, res, next) => {})     // app.use is a HOF
```

